His ministry and the National Treasury said on July 16 they would mobilise the additional $600 million the bankrupt airline's administrators said is needed to effect the rescue. In a July 17 Twitter posting Finance Minister Tito Mboweni denied planning to bail out SAA. "What government has committed to is to mobilise funding," Gordhan said in an interview with eNCA. "Now where it comes from, the form is comes is something that is still being worked on". --News24--